<h1>Aerialway</h1>

<p>This is used to tag different forms of transportation for people or goods by using aerial wires. For example these may include cable-cars, chair-lifts and drag-lifts. See the page Aerialway for more information on the usage of these tags.</p>

<p>[<b>cable_car</b>=<b><img src="images/g___px_Osm_element_way.svg.png"/></b>]<img src="images/images______Wikipedia___px.png"/>&#32;Cablecar or Tramway. Just one or two large cars. The traction cable forms a loop, but the cars do not loop around, they just move up and down on their own side, rolling along static cables over which they are suspended.<img src="images/__Aerialway_gondola_render.png"/></p>

<p>[<b>gondola</b>=<b><img src="images/g___px_Osm_element_way.svg.png"/></b>]<img src="images/images______Wikipedia___px.png"/>&#32;Gondola lift. Many cars on a looped cable.<img src="images/__Aerialway_gondola_render.png"/></p>

<p>[<b>chair_lift</b>=<b><img src="images/g___px_Osm_element_way.svg.png"/></b>]<img src="images/images______Wikipedia___px.png"/>&#32;Chairlift. Looped cable with a series of single chairs (typically seating two or four people, but can be more). Exposed to the open air (can have a bubble). This implies oneway=yes (drawn upward).  Any two-way chairlifts should be tagged oneway=no.<img src="images/______Chair_lift_rendering.png"/></p>

<p>[<b>mixed_lift</b>=<b><img src="images/g___px_Osm_element_way.svg.png"/></b>]<img src="images/images______Wikipedia___px.png"/>&#32;Mixed lift Also known as a hybrid lift is a new type of ski lift that combines the elements of a chairlift and a gondola lift.</p>

<p>[<b>drag_lift</b>=<b><img src="images/g___px_Osm_element_way.svg.png"/></b>]<img src="images/images______Wikipedia___px.png"/>&#32;Drag lift or Surface lift is an overhead tow-line for skiers and riders. A T-bar lift, button lift, or more simple looped rope drag lifts, or loops of wire with handles to grab. See also aerialway=t-bar, aerialway=j-bar, aerialway=platter and aerialway=rope_tow. This automatically implies oneway=yes (drawn upward).<img src="images/______Chair_lift_rendering.png"/></p>

<p>[<b>t-bar</b>=<b><img src="images/g___px_Osm_element_way.svg.png"/></b>]<img src="images/images______Wikipedia___px.png"/>&#32;T-bar lift.  A type of aerialway=drag_lift. This automatically implies oneway=yes (drawn upward).<img src="images/______Chair_lift_rendering.png"/></p>

<p>[<b>j-bar</b>=<b><img src="images/g___px_Osm_element_way.svg.png"/></b>]<img src="images/images______Wikipedia___px.png"/>&#32;J-bar lift. A type of aerialway=drag_lift. Like t-bar but just on one side. This automatically implies oneway=yes (drawn upward).<img src="images/______Chair_lift_rendering.png"/></p>

<p>[<b>platter</b>=<b><img src="images/g___px_Osm_element_way.svg.png"/></b>]<img src="images/images______Wikipedia___px.png"/>&#32;Platter lift. A type of aerialway=drag_lift. Similar to a t-bar, but with a disc instead of a bar. Single-person only. This automatically implies oneway=yes (drawn upward).<img src="images/______Chair_lift_rendering.png"/></p>

<p>[<b>rope_tow</b>=<b><img src="images/g___px_Osm_element_way.svg.png"/></b>]<img src="images/images______Wikipedia___px.png"/>&#32;Rope tow. A type of aerialway=drag_lift. This automatically implies oneway=yes (drawn upward).<img src="images/______Chair_lift_rendering.png"/></p>

<p>[<b>magic_carpet</b>=<b><img src="images/g___px_Osm_element_way.svg.png"/></b>]<img src="images/images______Wikipedia___px.png"/>&#32;Magic carpet. A type of ski lift. This automatically implies oneway=yes (drawn upward).</p>

<p>[<b>zip_line</b>=<b><img src="images/g___px_Osm_element_way.svg.png"/></b>]<img src="images/images______Wikipedia___px.png"/>&#32;Zip line. Simple aerial rope slides. This automatically implies oneway=yes (drawn downward).</p>

<p>[<b>pylon</b>=<b><img src="images/___px_Osm_element_node.svg.png"/></b>]<img src="images/images______Wikipedia___px.png"/>&#32;Aerial lift pylon is a pylon supporting the aerialway cable.</p>

<p>[<b>station</b>=<b><img src="images/___px_Osm_element_node.svg.png"/></b>]A station, where passengers can enter and/or leave the aerialway. Alternatively mapped according to the Public transport schema.</p>

<p>[<b>canopy</b>=<b><img src="images/g___px_Osm_element_way.svg.png"/></b>]Obsolete, please use aerialway=zip_line instead. This automatically implies oneway=yes (drawn downward).</p>

<p>[<b>goods</b>=<b><img src="images/g___px_Osm_element_way.svg.png"/></b>]Controversial, consider other aerialway=* values in combination with foot=no and/or a usage=* key instead of this.<img src="images/mages_c_cb_Aerialway_goods.png"/></p>

<p>[<b>user defined</b>=<b><img src="images/___px_Osm_element_node.svg.png"/><img src="images/g___px_Osm_element_way.svg.png"/></b>]All commonly used values according to Taginfo</p>
